$ Excel VBA: Worksheet.Visible

A → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Worksheet can be hidden by setting its property `.visible` to `xlSheetHidden` or `xlSheetVeryHidden`. If it is «only» hidden, the user sees the sheet name when right-clicking on any sheet name in the bottom of Excel.
If the sheet is «very hidden», the user doesn't see the sheet anymore by clicking there.

To show a sheet again with → development/languages/VBA, the property must be set to `xlSheetVisible`.
-
In the GUI, the visibility can be set in the → Microsoft/Office/Visual-Basic-Editor (→ Microsoft/Office/Excel#excel-key-shortcut[keyboard shortcut] `alt+F11`) in the properties sheet object (found under *Microsoft Excel Objects*).


sa:
  The → https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/office/vba/api/excel.xlsheetvisibility[`xlSheetVisibility`] enumeration.

  The `→ Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Worksheet` object.
